sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Mobile App
    participant API as FastAPI Routes
    participant SH as ShadowService
    participant CMD as CommandService
    participant DB as PostgreSQL device_shadows and commands
    participant MQ as Mosquitto Broker
    participant ESP as ESP32 Firmware
    participant RX as MQTT Handlers
    participant TEL as TelemetryService
    participant TSDB as TimescaleDB

    C->>API: REST request set desired state or command
    API->>SH: Update desired shadow
    SH->>DB: Persist desired plus version
    API->>CMD: Send device command
    CMD->>DB: Persist command record
    CMD->>MQ: Publish tankctl device_id command
    MQ->>ESP: Deliver command
    Note right of ESP: Idempotency guard rejects stale command versions

    ESP->>MQ: Publish reported state
    ESP->>MQ: Publish heartbeat
    ESP->>MQ: Publish telemetry

    MQ->>RX: Route by topic channel
    RX->>SH: reported or heartbeat updates
    SH->>DB: Persist reported and reconcile state
    RX->>TEL: telemetry payload
    TEL->>TSDB: Store telemetry metric

    loop Background reconcile
        API->>SH: Scheduler checks desired vs reported
        SH->>MQ: Re-publish pending command when needed
    end
